---+ About This Document

%ICON{hand}% This document is for system administrators and grid users. It explains how to use the %LINK_OIM% to register users, resources, virtual organizations and vital contacts with the [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/GlossaryG#DefsGridOperationsCenter][Grid Operations Center (GOC)]].

---+ Requirements

   1. All procedures require a personal [[ReleaseDocumentation/UserCertificate][PKI/X509 security certificate]] that has been issued for you to use for personal identification by one of the [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/GlossaryC#DefsCA][Certificate Authorities (CAs)]] trusted by the %LINK_OSG%. There is information about which [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/GlossaryC#DefsCA][CAs]] we accept on [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/CaDistribution][this page]] and how to get a new certificate on [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/ReleaseDocumentation/CertificateUserGet][this page]].
   1. You must additionally have some way of managing your certificate, such as a browser that will import it directly, a mac keychain and keychain-compatible browser, or some other kind of certificate manager and its appropriate browser.

---+ How to register a Person with the OIM?

| Step in Process | Explanation | 
| 1. Entering the OIM Portal | The user approaches the OIM portal with their web browser. | 
| 2. Is there an OSG [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/GlossaryC#DefsCA][CA]] issued Cert in the browser? | If a certificate is present, OIM will examine the certificate and compare it to the current registration data. If not, the user will be prompted to return to the site with an OSG [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/GlossaryC#DefsCA][CA]] issued certificate loaded in the browser. |
| 3. Is [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/GlossaryD#DefsDistinguishedName][DN]] already in OIM? | If the user&amp;rsquo;s [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/GlossaryD#DefsDistinguishedName][Distinguished Name (DN)]] that appears on his or her certificate is already entered in OIM, then the user has already been approved by the [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/GlossaryG#DefsGridOperationsCenter][GOC]]. An approved member may change registration information for any entities for which he or she is listed as an associated contact (administrative, security, miscellaneous, etc). If not, the user is prompted to enter personal information. |
| 4. User inputs Personal Info? | The user is required to enter information for [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Documentation/GlossaryG#DefsGridOperationsCenter][GOC]] approval of her or his OIM membership. Detailed explanation of the requirements of this form can be found [[https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Operations/OIMRegistrationInstructions#Registering_Yourself][here.]]  After the information has been completed, the account is active. |

